      "content": "There is mixed evidence regarding deterrence, and many modern experts are moving past the idea of simple, punitive deterrence. While strict sentencing *can* reduce recidivism in certain contexts, the overwhelming focus in contemporary policy is on addressing root causes like poverty and lack of opportunity. Therefore, the current consensus leans toward rehabilitative and preventative measures as being more effective long-term than simply increasing incarceration rates.",
